Steps.Message: Update at 19:22 - This is Rob from the messaging team again. I'm happy to inform you that power to all but one property in the Ringmer area should now be back on. Our engineers have diverted power safely back to the vast majority of customers. However, due to the location and complexity of the issue, we have also used temporary generators to restore power to some properties. These will provide power until our engineers plan in and safely complete the full repair, which may take a few days. We're really sorry for any disruption this caused. If your power isn't on or there's anything you'd like to talk to us about, call us on 08003163105, free from landlines and mobiles.

We became aware of this power cut at 14:05. We’re sorry for any disruption this may have caused you. We didn’t know in advance there would be a power cut, but now that we know, our teams will do everything they can to get your power back quickly. Engineers in our control room have switched some customers power back on in your area. To get everyone’s power back on we may need to attend to investigate and make repairs. We’ll continue to update you until everyone’s power is back on.
Steps.Name: We are restoring customers automatically

Steps.Message: We have engineers on their way. As this is affecting your area, they will not need to attend your property. Rest assured once they arrive, they’ll work as quickly as is safely possible to get your power back on.
Steps.Name: Engineers on their way

Steps.Message: Engineers are now on site, carrying out investigations into the fault. Once they have completed their assessment, they will carry out repairs.
Steps.Name: Engineers investigating and fixing
